<H3> <TI>   Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Construction Minister Morimoto </H4>

<F P=102> OW2804121694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0951 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 28 KYODO -- Martial arts expert Koji 
Morimoto, considered a specialist in commerce and industry 
issues in Komeito [Clean Government Party], was given the 
construction minister's portfolio. He replaced Kozo Igarashi of 
the Social Democratic Party (SDP). 
  Morimoto, 52, has been elected to the House of 
Representatives four times by his Nara Prefecture constituency 
and has served as an executive on the lower house's Steering 
Committee. 
  Since the launching of the previous coalition government 
last 
August, Morimoto has been in charge of the party's Diet 
management. Morimoto's post has put him in a position to 
confront the opposition Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) in 
negotiations. 
  He is a close ally of party Secretary General Yuichi 
Ichikawa, a coalition strategist. 
  Morimoto speaks in an undisguised Kansai dialect that 
characterizes the natives of the Osaka-Kyoto-Nara district and 
has been described as a gentle, considerate type in 
interpersonal affairs. His gentle demeanor and refusal to utter 
any complaints should not be confused with a lack of resolve, 
however, since Morimoto is an honorary fourth degree black belt 
holder in nihon kenpo, a modern version of kung fu. 
  In the residence for Diet members, Morimoto's room is 
crowded 
with physical training machines and the Kansai University 
graduate also swims regularly to stay in shape. 

</TEXT>

