<H3> <TI>   Public Works Monitoring Committees Created </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Public Works Monitoring Committees Created </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2804091694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0841 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 28 KYODO -- The Construction Ministry 
has set up special monitoring committees for securing fairness 
in biddings for public works projects in all of its eight 
regional construction bureaus, ministry officials said Thursday 
[28 April]. 
  The committees will keep watch on the procedures for 
biddings 
and receive complaints from companies that fail to get 
contracts, the officials said. 
  The move came in response to a series of major corruption 
scandals, which exposed rampant, illegal collusion between 
politicians and big builders to fix public works contracts and 
deflect official investigation into bid-rigging. 
  The committees, which comprise five experts, will advise the 
ministry's local branch heads. 
  They will monitor and assess fairness of the qualifications 
for bidders for the public works contracts given by the local 
construction bureaus. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

