<H3> <TI>   Ministry on `Major Revision' of Stopgap Budget </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry on `Major Revision' of Stopgap Budget </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2804110994 Tokyo KYODO in English 1040 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 28 KYODO -- The Finance Ministry plans 
to make a major revision in the stopgap budget for fiscal 1994 
because of a delay expected in Diet proceedings on the full 
budget for the year, ministry officials said Thursday [28 
April]. They said the revision is required since substantive 
debates on the full budget by the House of Representatives 
Budget Committee are unlikely to start until mid-May. 
  The stopgap budget for the year that started April 1, 
compiled to deal with the nation's political confusion, is valid 
only until May 20. The officials said the full budget is 
unlikely to be approved by the Diet before that date. 
  The new stopgap budget will be valid until sometime in the 
40-day period through June 29, when the current Diet session 
ends, and will involve additional appropriations of 3 trillion 
yen to 4 trillion yen, the officials said. 
  The fiscal 1994 budget was submitted to the Diet on March 4, 
but there have been no Diet debates on it because of the 
political confusion. 

</TEXT>

