<H3> <TI>   Prince Yuveakneat Said To Succeed Sihanouk </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prince Yuveakneat Said To Succeed Sihanouk </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2704045494 Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA in Cambodian 27 
Apr 94 pp 1, 2 </F>

<F P=103> BK2704045494 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA </F>
<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] No one knows when Prince Kromluong [Norodom] 
Yuveakneat will leave the monkhood. 
  According to unofficial sources, Prince Kromluong Yuveakneat 
wished to enter the Buddhist priesthood for just two days, but 
until now he has not yet left. 
  Before returning to the United States, a daughter of Prince 
Kromluong Yuveakneat told REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA at Unalaom 
Monastery that her father will not return to the United States 
but will stay on in Cambodia. She and her mother will leave for 
the United States on 22 April. [passage omitted] 
  His majesty the king has been very pleased with the 
ordination of Prince Kromluong Yuveakneat, who is his elder son. 
  Whether this ordination will be for the short or long term, 
the Prince Kromluong will be fulfilling his wish to show his 
gratitude to his father, His Majesty Norodom Sihanouk Varaman, 
king of the Kingdom of Cambodia, who is the father of the nation. 
  Since his first return to the Kingdom of Cambodia, the 
Prince 
Kromluong has paid great attention to improving and solving the 
difficult livelihood of children in orphanages. He has also 
given love and care to the children living and studying in 
temples. 
  Analysts say that his simple manner could make him the 
successor to the throne. It is not known what role is the 
Prince Kromluong playing in Cambodia. 

</TEXT>

