<F P=101> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ranariddh on Roundtable Meeting With KR </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ranariddh on Roundtable Meeting With KR </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2804063894 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0500 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2804063894 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0500 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At a meeting on 27 April with foreign diplomats 
accredited to the Kingdom of Cambodia, Prince Krompreah Norodom 
Ranariddh, first prime minister of the Royal Government of 
Cambodia [RGC], said that the RGC respects and fully supports 
the initiative of His Majesty King Norodom Sihanouk, king of 
Cambodia, on the coming roundtable meeting in the royal palace. 
  The prince krompreah further said that this roundtable is a 
meeting between the RGC and the Khmer Rouge [KR] and not talks. 
He clearly specified that the RGC will do all it can for the 
roundtable meeting to proceed smoothly by ensuring 100 percent 
security and safety. The prince krompreah said that if the 
roundtable meeting did not achieve results, a consultation will 
be held with the cochairmen of the Paris international 
conference to implement the third part of the Paris agreement. 
  Concerning the Khmer Rouge's abduction of some foreigners in 
rural areas, Prince Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh promised to work 
for the safe return of these foreigners to Phnom Penh. 

</TEXT>

