<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Khmer Rouge Activities Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Khmer Rouge Activities Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Success at Pailin Updated </H4>

<F P=102> BK2804062594 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2804062594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Here is an additional report from the Pailin 
battlefield on 27 April. 
  On 27 april, we launched a sweep operation against the 
two-headed elements along Route 10 beginning from the west. 
After fighting for the whole day from 0600 at dawn to 0630 in 
the evening, we smashed and liberated the 4th Division command 
post at Treng on Route 10. This area has been a strategic 
position of the communist Vietnamese, communist Vietnamese 
puppets, and two-headed government since 1979. Treng, the 
bridgehead of the defense line of Battambang town, has vanished. 
  Hul Savoan, four-star general and commander of Battambang's 
5th Military Region, who fled from Pailin to hide in Treng after 
being routed, has disappeared from this area. 
  We also totally swept the enemy positions at Phlov Meas and 
Phum Tuol. We seized four 37-mm, three 76.2-mm, and six 12.7-mm 
artillery pieces and a large quantity of small guns. 
  We are pushing forward. 

</TEXT>

