<H4>    Official on Battambang Campaign </H4>

<F P=102> BK2704055194 Phnom Penh AKP in French 0400 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2704055194 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh 27 Apr (AKP) -- Some 40 Khmer Rouge [KR] 
rebels recently infiltrated Andeuk Hep commune in Ratanakmondol 
District of Battambang Province. They robbed many houses and 
took away four rifles belonging to local militiamen. 
  During the night of the same day the Khmer Rouge left this 
commune and spread out in Chrap area with the intention of 
attacking Ratanakmondol District and Snoeng commune. Half of 
the local population took refuge in neighboring districts 
(Battambang and Bavel). 
  According to Battambang District Police Chief, a group of 30 
Khmer Rouge on 20 April infiltrated into Battambang District 
with the intention of launching attacks. 
  In Ek Phnum District, about 30 Khmer Rouge, under the 
command 
of Sok, retreated from Boeng Thmar and Kbal Chor positions in 
the direction of Pailin area. 

</TEXT>

