  [Text] On 17 April, hundreds of people living along the 
Tonle Sap Lake assaulted the Vietnamese at (Kbal Taol) and (Kaoh 
Khsach Pouy), killing 30 of them and destroying three motor 
boats and four (?fishing) boats. 
  The report said that during the current fishing season, the 
Vietnamese have arrogantly prohibited our Cambodian people from 
fishing in this area. The Vietnamese aggressors have killed 
many Cambodians who went fishing in this area. 
  The Cambodian people have time and again complained to the 
authorities in this region but to no avail, because these 
authorities who are lackeys of the Vietnamese think only of 
serving their Vietnamese masters. Therefore, the people say 
that their only alternative is to settle the Vietnamese acts of 
aggression and expansion along Tonle Sap Lake by themselves. 

