<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   SRV Foreign Minister on Refugee Repatriation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SRV Foreign Minister on Refugee Repatriation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2704131194 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2704131194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Speaking at Jakarta's Wisma Negara Guest House this 
afternoon, Vietnamese Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam 
reiterated his country's commitment to repatriate Vietnamese 
refugees still held on Galang Island. Even though he did not 
give an exact deadline for the repatriation, the Vietnamese 
minister said his government will do its best to find an early 
solution to the issue. About 8,000 Vietnamese refugees remain at 
the Galang island holding center. 

</TEXT>

