<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seoul, Moscow Promoting Cooperation in Weaponry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seoul, Moscow Promoting Cooperation in Weaponry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2704125394 Seoul YONHAP in English 1204 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2704125394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 27 (YONHAP) -- South Korea and Russia 
have in principle agreed to mutually cooperate in the area of 
weapons system and military technology, a government official 
said on Wednesday. 
  He said Foreign and Defense Ministries are having close 
talks 
with their respective Russian counterparts based on the 
agreement. 
  "As part of cooperation in the military area, the two 
countries are currently studying the possible joint production 
of Russia's ultra-modern weapons," the official said. 
  He elaborated that in joint production, Russia will furnish 
expertise and South Korea necessary capital and marketing. 
  The official added, however, that such cooperation would 
hardly be endorsed by a formal agreement. 
  He reasoned that Russia's defense industry is different from 
Korea's in technological style and therefore their weapons and 
knowhow in some areas cannot be transferred to South Korea as 
they are. 
  "It also is almost impossible at this stage for Korea to 
introduce Russia's military expertise in return for the debts 
Russia owes to South Korea in economic cooperation credits," he 
said. 

</TEXT>

