<H3> <TI>   President's Cabinet Reshuffle Previewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President's Cabinet Reshuffle Previewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2804032594 Seoul YONHAP in English 0310 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2804032594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 28 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam 
will name a new deputy prime minister and head of the National 
Unification Board (NUB), and possibly a few other cabinet 
members, if the National Assembly approves the appointment of Yi 
Yong-tok as prime minister by Thursday. 
  President Kim could carry out a partial cabinet reshuffle in 
consultation with Yi Yong-tok, who replaces Yi Hoe-chang, within 
Thursday. [sentence as received] 
  Parliamentary approval of the new prime minister has been 
stalled at the National Assembly over two other controversial 
issues. But it appeared possible that the Assembly would 
approve Yi Yong-tok's appointment during its plenary session 
which opens at 2 p.m. Thursday. 
  President Kim will then immediately hand credentials to Yi 
at 
Chongwadade [presidential office] and begin consultations to 
select, among others, Yi's successor as deputy prime minister 
and NUB minister, a Chongwadae official said. 
  If National Assembly approval comes later, a partial cabinet 
reshuffle will take place Friday morning, sources said. 
  President Kim will hold a cabinet meeting Friday. 

</TEXT>

