<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Official on IAEA `Preconditions' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Official on IAEA `Preconditions' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2704065594 Seoul SEOUL SINMUN in Korean 27 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK2704065594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul SEOUL SINMUN </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Pak Chong-hyon from Paris] </F>
  [Text] As an International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] 
inspection team's visit to Pyongyang has been delayed, the North 
Korean Embassy in Vienna reported on 26 April: "If an IAEA 
inspection team does not arrive in Pyongyang by 28 April, the 
deadline for witnessing the replacement of fuel rods, we will 
have no choice but to remove the seals and replace the fuel 
rods." In this way, North Korea strongly hinted that it would 
proceed with the replacement at all costs. 
  Yun Ho-chin, a counselor at the North Korean Embassy in 
Vienna, said over the telephone: "We proposed that the 
inspection team observe the fuel rod replacement, and the IAEA 
presented eight preconditions." He also said: "These 
conditions were presented to ask us to abide by the Nuclear 
Safeguards Accord. Therefore, we cannot accept them." 

</TEXT>

