<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Five Power Defense Arrangement Exercises Begin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Five Power Defense Arrangement Exercises Begin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2604100794 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 
GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2604100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fighter planes and warships from five nations 
started mock air and sea battles off Malaysia and Singapore 
today to test the region's only multilateral defense pact 
involving outside powers. The four-day joint air and sea 
exercises under the Five Power Defense Arrangement -- FPDA -- 
end on Friday. FPDA link Britain, Australia, New Zealand, 
Malaysia, and Singapore. All are members of the Commonwealth. 
Code-named ADEX 94-2, the exercise is taking place over 
Singapore and Malaysia and the South China Sea, an area of 
overlapping territorial claims. The exercise was coordinated 
from the Royal Malaysian Air Force base at Butterworth, 
headquarters of the Integrated Air Defense System. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

