<H3> <TI>   SDPJ To Join Sakigake, Others in Floor Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDPJ To Join Sakigake, Others in Floor Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2904043094 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 29 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2904043094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 29 April Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] In a NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN interview on 28 April, 
Chairman Tomiichi Murayama of the Social Democratic Party of 
Japan [SDPJ] showed a positive attitude toward formation of a 
joint floor group with Sakigake [Harbinger] and some other 
groups. He noted the SDPJ will formally seek formation of the 
SDPJ-Sakigake floor group at the lower house after Golden Week 
recess in May, opening party head and executive talks on a 
regular basis. He said: "We would like to open formal talks 
with Sakigake after the recess in May." 
  In the interview, Murayama stressed the need for the joint 
floor group with the Sakigake, saying: "We should build closer 
relations with Sakigake." On top of that, he hinted at his 
positive attitude toward a tie-up with certain quarters in the 
Japan New Party and the Democratic Socialist Party, noting: "In 
addition to Sakigake, we would like to seek cooperation with 
other people we can get along with." 

</TEXT>

