<H3> <TI>   Council Studies Complaints on Market Opening </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council Studies Complaints on Market Opening </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2904040194 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 26 Apr 
94 Morning Edition p 5--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2904040194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 25 April, the government held a meeting of the 
"Council for Promotion of Processing Market Opening Complaints" 
(generally known as the Ombudsman Council and led by Chairman 
Yoshio Ogawara), which is composed of civilians who are 
non-government officials, to discuss how to deal with 26 cases 
of complaints connected with the standards and approval system. 
At the meeting, participants confirmed that actions had been 
decided on 24 cases. Among actions to be taken are: 
Deregulation on activities of lawyers specialized in foreign 
legal affairs; changes in food product labels to have the 
expiration date indicated; and improvement of customs procedures 
for handling imported cargoes after business hours. Regarding 
safety standards of helicopters and specifications of water 
supply equipment, it was decided that from the standpoint of 
promoting imports, the council will continue to study the 
possibility of easing standards. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

