<H3> <TI>   Delegate Discusses Economic Talks With PRC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegate Discusses Economic Talks With PRC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2804162494 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1359 GMT 28 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2804162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["New Step in Friendly Relations" -- MONTSAME headline] </F>
  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 28 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Under such 
heading the newspaper "ARDYN ERH" publishes today an interview 
of the deputy head of the National Development Department L. 
Demberel who is taking part in the forthcoming III [as received] 
meeting of the inter-governmental Mongolian-Chinese Commission 
on Economic, Trade, Scientific and Technical Cooperation as a 
deputy head of the Mongolian delegation. 
  The trade and economic relations between Mongolia and China, 
he said, have been increasingly intensifying over a few last 
years. Just for the period from 1991 to 1993 the trade turnover 
between the two countries has increased nearly three fold. The 
government of the People's Republic of China (PRC) has granted 
to Mongolia during the years of 1991, 1992 disinterested credits 
worth 80 million yuan as well as commodities and gratis 
financial assistance. 
  In the course of the visit of the premier of the State 
Council of the PRC, he noted also, it is expected to sign a 
treaty on friendly relations and cooperation between Mongolia 
and the PRC, agreements on economic and technical cooperation, 
on granting by the Chinese Government gratis aid to Mongolia, 
cooperation on examining the quality of importing and exporting 
commodities mutually being supplied between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

