<H3> <TI>   Intelligence Chief Charged To Improve Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Intelligence Chief Charged To Improve Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2804161494 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1401 GMT 28 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2804161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 28 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
newspaper "ARDYN ERH" informs that the head of the Central 
Intelligence Board (CIB) of Mongolia has been charged by the 
prosecutor general of Mongolia to strengthen the actions of the 
board for ensuring security. In an official paper addressing 
himself it was said that on the pages of newspapers came to be 
published some copies of the secret documents pertaining to the 
classified or even top secret information. Thus there has been 
created unfavourable conditions in reference to the state 
security. 
  The document stresses the significance of strengthening the 
efficient arrangement of the work of the CIB for investigating 
such actions bearing a criminal nature as the divulgence of the 
state top secrets through the mass media and the losing of 
secret papers as well. 

</TEXT>

