<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Creation of Development Foundation Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Creation of Development Foundation Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704132594 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1230 GMT 27 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2704132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 27 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- At the 
press conference held here for Mongolian and foreign newsmen 
there has been announced about the creation of the Foundation 
for Development of Mongolia named after Joseph Laidey [name as 
received]. As was said by the founders, the new foundation is 
sets itself the goal of propagating the ideas by the US scholar 
Joseph Laidey put forth in 1857 the hypothesis claiming that it 
was Mongolia that was the cradle of humankind on our planet. 
  Besides this main goal the foundation is to promote the 
development of Mongolistics, preservation of the values of the 
nomadic civilization and especially its ecological culture. 
  It was reported at the press conference also that the 
founders of the foundation made up by more than 12 public 
organizations of the country are intending to institute the 
prize named after Joseph Laidey which is to be awarded to 
Mongolian and foreign scholars, figures of culture, art and 
literature for their contribution to the distinctive development 
of the Central Asia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

