<H3> <TI>   Government Repatriates Cabodian, Lao Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Repatriates Cabodian, Lao Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2904102394 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2904102394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Thailand repatriated a total of 998 Cambodians and 
some 400 Lao refugees and displaced persons this week. 
  The Ministry of Foreign Affairs said the Cambodians mainly 
comprise children, women, and the elderly, who fled the war in 
Cambodia to Ta Phraya District of Prachin Buri Province. They 
were sheltered temporily in an area of 5 rai provided by the 
Thai Government. The area is about two kilometers from the 
Cambodian border. 
  Meanwhile, Secretary General of the National Security 
Council 
Khachatphai Burutphat said more than 400 Lao refugees and 
displaced persons were repatriated yesterday through the 
Thai-Lao Friendship Bridge. It is the highest number of Laos 
returnees repatriated from the Thai soil this year. 
  The Lao refugees and displaced persons are all the Hmong 
hilltribe people who were sheltered at the Ban Napho 
repatriation center in Nakhon Phanom Province. 
  The National Security Council plans to close the 
repatriation 
center within the end of this year. 

</TEXT>

