<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Intellectual Property Memo Signed With Vietnam </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Intellectual Property Memo Signed With Vietnam </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2704120494 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2704120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Thailand and Vietnam signed a memorandum of 
understanding on intellectual property, the first of its kind 
between the two developing countries in this fast-growing region 
of the world. 
  The document was signed by representatives from Thailand's 
Ministry of Commerce and Vietnam's Ministry of Science, 
Technology and Environment during the visit by Deputy Minister 
of Commerce Churin Laksanawisit to Vietnam during April 22 to 
24, 1994. 
  The agreement is aimed at making Thailand a center for 
intellectual property registration and claims for Indochina. 
  Deputy Minister Churin said that Vietnam is in agreement in 
Thailand's proposal. 
  The memorandum of standing signed by the two sides provided 
opportunities for both countries to exchange information on 
laws, procedures in registration of patents, trademarks, and 
copyrights, registrated marks and patents, and cooperation in 
personnel development. 
  Churin said that the signing of the memorandum of 
understanding with Vietnam will benefit Thai business people and 
investors, facilitating the registration of their trademarks and 
protecting their intellectual property rights. 

</TEXT>

