<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yamaha Motor Establishes New Firm in Taiwan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yamaha Motor Establishes New Firm in Taiwan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204104894 Tokyo KYODO in English 1022 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2204104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 22 KYODO -- Yamaha Motor Co., Japan's 
leading motorcycle manufacturer, said Friday [22 April] it has 
established a new firm in Taipei to boost motorcycle shipping 
capacity from Taiwan. 
  The new firm, called Yamaha Motor Taiwan Trading Co., is 
part 
of Yamaha Motor's strategy to make Taiwan a globally important 
production site of small motorcycles. 
  Yamaha has produced 400,000 motorcycles annually at its 
local 
venture, Yamaha Motor Taiwan Co. of the total, 20,000 to 50,000 
units have been shipped yearly to Europe and Asia, including 
Japan. 
  The new firm was capitalized at 32 million yen, with 75 
percent of equity shares owned by Yamaha Motor of Japan and the 
remainder by Yamaha Motor Taiwan, it said. 

</TEXT>

