<F P=102>   SK2704043794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0421 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2704043794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 27 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists 
staged an air war exercise against the North Monday in the skies 
above Umsong, Tokjok Islet, Wonju and Yongwol, South Korea, with 
Pacific-based U.S. fighters and some 200 fighter-bombers, 
assault planes, observation planes and helicopter gunships 
belonging to the U.S. Air Force in South Korea and the puppet 
airforce under the command of an E-3 early warning plane, 
military sources said. 
  On the same day, the South Korean puppets held a firing 
exercise and a helicopter operation exercise as part of the 
Hwarang war exercise in a frontline area adjacent to the 
Demilitarized Zone along the Military Demarcation Line. 
  The premeditated military provocations are rendering the 
situation on the Korean peninsula more strained. 
  If the United States and the South Korean rulers 
continuously 
reinforce their aggression forces and unleash a nuclear war on 
the Korean peninsula, the provokers will never get off scotfree. 

</TEXT>

