<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 29 (KCNA) -- The scheme to 
reinforce the Armed Forces in South Korea, on top of tens of 
thousands of U.S. troops and up-to-date means of war deployed 
there, shows that the United States has not abandoned its 
intention to stifle the DPRK by military strength, taking issue 
with the fictitious "nuclear issue" of the DPRK, says NODONG 
