lever in executing its Asia-Pacific policy. U.S. arms buildup 
in South Korea is motivated by the strategic aim to strengthen 
its domination over Asia and the Pacific with force. 
  "North Korea's surprise attack" advertised by the United 
States is nothing but a sophism to justify arms buildup in South 
Korea. 
  The United States' reinforcement of armament in South Korea 
poses a serious threat to the peace and security of the Korean 
peninsula and the Asian-Pacific region. 
  The United States must stop arms buildup in South Korea, not 
ignoring the desire of the people in this region for 
independence and peace. 

</TEXT>

