BFN 

<F P=106> ["The United States Must Promptly Renounce Its Hostile </F>
Policy Against the DPRK" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 28 (KCNA) -- Foreign political 
parties urged the United States to promptly renounce its hostile 
policy toward the Democratic People's Republic of Korea aimed at 
isolating and stifling it. 
  Vassalo Anthony Joseph, general secretary of the Central 
Committee of the Communist Party of Malta, in a letter to the 
president of the UN General Assembly April 3 urged him to show 
deep interest in the resumption of DPRK-USA talks and pay due 
attention to the challenging act of the United States in 
unilaterally foiling the third round of DPRK-USA talks. 
  The letter strongly urged that the United States should 
withdraw all its military hardware including nuclear weapons and 
troops from South Korea and stop any manner of interference in 
the internal affairs of Korea including military action. 
  Amaral Matos, first secretary of the Maputo City Committee 
of 
