said the United States could never frighten Korea although it 
was putting unreasonable pressure on it in conspiracy with the 
International Atomic Energy Agency. 
  The statement warned that if the United States continue to 
resort to pressure on Korea with an anachronistic daydream, it 
would sustain a more ignominious defeat and meet with 
condemnations from the world people. 
  The Polish League of Communists "Proletariat" in a statement 
April 9 denounced the United States' hostile Korea policy aimed 
at isolating and stifling the DPRK and expressed full support to 
the recent steps taken by the DPRK with regard to the "nuclear 
issue" and to its stand manifested in them. 

</TEXT>

