<H3> <TI>   Rallies Protest ROK Nuclear Waste Dumping </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rallies Protest ROK Nuclear Waste Dumping </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2704044694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0435 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2704044694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 27 (KCNA) -- Mass rallies are being 
held across the northern half of Korea to denounce the criminal 
dumping of nuclear waste by the South Korean rulers. 
  At a mass rally held in Wonsan, a port city of culture and 
recreation on the East Coast, on April 23, the speakers said 
that the South Korean rulers had dumped into the sea nuclear 
waste amounting to 11,000 trillion becquerels, heavily 
destroying resources and causing women to give birth to deformed 
babies. 
  They bitterly condemned nuclear waste dumping as an 
anti-national, anti-human criminal act which can be committed 
only by those indifferent to the existence of the nation and 
heedless of international law. 
  The speakers at a mass rally held in Nampo, a port city on 
the West Coast, on April 26 said that the Korean people would 
never tolerate the heinous crimes of the Kim Yong-sam group 
reducing even the seas to a nuclear dumping ground, not 
contented with covering the whole land of the South with nuclear 
weapons of outside forces. 
  They stressed that all the compatriots at home and abroad 
will wage a more vigorous anti-U.S., anti-war, anti-nuke 
struggle to check nuclear waste dumping by the South Korean 
puppet clique and make the Korean peninsula a nuclear-free, 
peace zone without the danger of war. 

</TEXT>

