<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundtable on Denuclearization Held in Japan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundtable on Denuclearization Held in Japan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2804151494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1503 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2804151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo April 26 (KNS-KCNA) [dateline as received] -- 
A Japan-Korea emergency round-table conversation on the 
denuclearisation of the Korean peninsula and the nuclear issue 
was held in Nagoya city on April 13 under the sponsorship of the 
Aichi Prefectural People's Council for Japan-Korea Friendship. 
  Mitsudoshi Omatsuzawa, secretary general of the Aichi 
prefectural headquarters of the Japan Social-Democratic Party, 
addressing the round-table conversation, said the joint 
declaration on the conversion of Northeast Asia into a 
nuclear-free, peace zone, which was issued between the Japan 
Social-Democratic Party and the Workers' Party of Korea in March 
1981, is of weighty significance at present. 
  Noting that the Japan Social-Democratic Party assumes a 
heavy 
responsibility in making the Japanese Government approach the 
settlement of the problem with a right stand under the overflow 
of the informations slandering the Democratic People's Republic 
of Korea over the nuclear issue, he stressed the Japan 
Social-Democratic Party would support the independent, peaceful 
reunification of Korea. 

</TEXT>

