<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-083 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  27 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Offices in Osaka Raided by Police </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Offices in Osaka Raided by Police </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Police Search Denounced </H4>

<F P=102> SK2704044494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0427 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2704044494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 25 (KNS-KCNA) -- Chief vice-chairman of 
the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of 
Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon), Ho Chong-man, called an 
emergency press conference in Tokyo on April 25 regarding the 
forcible search of the Osaka Prefectural headquarters and 
branches of Chongnyon by the Japanese police, at which he read 
out a statement in the name of the Chongnyon Central Standing 
Committee. 
  The statment said: 
  At about 07:20 on April 25, the Osaka Prefectural police 
brought 56 mobile cars with more than 1,300 policemen to the 
prefectural headquarters of Chongnyon and made a forcible search 
of the headquarters' hall after creating an atmosphere of terror 
around the headquarters. 
  On the other hand, the Osaka Prefectural police forced the 
same search at branches of the Osaka Prefectural headquarters of 
Chongnyon. 
  The massive crackdown on the headquarters and branches of 
Chongnyon were the first of their kind in 39 years after the 
formation of Chongnyon. This shows how openly the Japanese 
authorities are suppressing Chongnyon. 
  Drawing attention to the fact that the Japanese reactionary 
authorities got more frantic in suppressing Chongnyon when 
nuclear row against the DPRK was being intensified, the 
statement said: 
  The Japanese Government must renounce at once its hostile 
policy towards the DPRK and repressive policy against the Korean 
residents in Japan. We demand that the Japanese Government and 
police stop immediately their unjustifiable suppression of 
Chongnyon and apologize for it. 
  We regard the illegal crackdown this time as a grave 
provocation against the Korean people. 
  On the same day, O Hyong-chin, vice-chairman of Chongnyon 
and 
chairman of its Osaka Prefectural headquarters, called a press 
conference and denounced the crackdown by the Japanese police. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7344 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas083_c_94015" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-083 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  28 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Offices in Osaka Raided by Police </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Offices in Osaka Raided by Police </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Korean Residents Protest Crackdown </H4>

<F P=102> SK2804152594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1514 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2804152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 28 (KCNA) -- Korean residents in 
Japan protested against the crackdown on the Osaka Prefectural 
Headquarters of the General Association of Korean Residents in 
Japan (Chongnyon) and its branches by Japanese police, according 
to KNS reports from Tokyo. 
  Representatives of the Federation of Korean Traders and 
Industrialists in Japan on April 26 demanded the Japan Police 
Agency to probe into the truth behind the murder of 
Vice-Chairman of the Federation Ku Cha-yong, saying that the 
forcible search into the Osaka prefectural headquarters of 
Chongnyon by Osaka prefectural police and assault on a Korean 
student are the result of the hostile policy of Japanese 
authorities towards the DPRK and Chongnyon. 
  On the same day, officials and compatriots under the Osaka 
prefectural headquarters of Chongnyon thronged to the Osaka 
prefectural police headquarters and strongly demanded it 
renounce at once the hostile policy towards the DPRK, stop 
suppressing Korean residents in Japan and apologize for it and 
immediately return the unconcerned materials seized from the 
Osaka prefectural headquarters of Chongnyon and its branches. 
  Song Chang-to, chairman of the Osaka Prefectural Committee 
of 
the Union of Korean Teachers in Japan, in his report at its 
emergency meeting on April 26, charged that the Japanese 
authorities made every effort to undermine the organizations of 
Koreans in Japan and obliterate the education of Koreans, before 
the war of aggression on Korea was unleashed by the U.S. 
imperialists in 1950, and called upon the teachers and students 
to cope with the subversive moves of the reactionaries within 
and without with heightened vigilance. 
  At the meeting, O Hyong-chin, vice-chairman of the Chongnyon 
Central Standing Committee and chairman of the Osaka prefectural 
headquarters of Chongnyon, called for smashing the subversive 
plots of the reactionaries within and without with united 
efforts and actively push ahead with the work. 
  Meanwhile, Vice-Chairman Paek Han-ki and director of 
International Department Kim Tae-hui of the Chongnyon Central 
Standing Committee met the cadres of Japan Social-Democratic 
Party [JSDP] on April 25 and asked for positive activities of 
the JSDP to stop the suppression of Chongnyon by the Japanese 
authorities and immediately renounce and rectify the hostile 
policy towards the DPRK. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7345 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas083_c_94016" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-083 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  28 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Offices in Osaka Raided by Police </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Offices in Osaka Raided by Police </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Anti-Chongnyon `Campaign' Condemned </H4>

<F P=102> SK2804115594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1108 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2804115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 28 (KCNA) -- We who regard the 
dignity of the country and the nation as our life and soul 
demand that the Japanese authorities immediately stop the 
repressive campaign against Koreans in Japan and the General 
Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) and warn 
that their indiscreet acts may cause grave unpardonable 
consequences against history and the times. 
  This is stressed in a statement issued today by the 
Korea-Japan Friendship Association. 
  The police authorities in Osaka Prefecture, Japan, some time 
ago surrounded the Osaka prefectural headquarters of Chongnyon 
with the mobilization of 1,300 police before forcibly searching 
the hall of the headquarters and its four branches in Osaka. 
And members of the "Kanto Council of the Union of Patriots of 
Great Japan" staged an anti-Chongnyon, anti-DPRK campaign in 
front of the headquarters of Chongnyon and organs under its 
affiliation. 
  This hostile campaign came at a time when the United States, 
Japan and the South Korean authorities were rendering the 
situation on the Korean peninsula extremely strained over the 
"nuclear issue" and the Japanese Government authorities were 
openly calling for setting in-motion an "international 
cooperation system" to stifle the DPRK, says the statement, 
bitterly denouncing it as an intolerable provocation against the 
DPRK as well as Chongnyon and Koreans in Japan. 
  The statement continues: 
  The Japanese authorities' repressive campaign against 
Chongnyon is a mockery of and an insult to the far-sighted and 
conscience-minded personages and people of Japan who are making 
all sincere efforts to establish relations of good neighbourhood 
with the DPRK and live on good terms with it. 
  We expect that the Dietmen's League for the Promotion of 
Japan-Korea Friendship and conscience-minded personages and 
other people of Japan will pay deep attention to the grave 
situation and take resolute measures lest the DPRK-Japan 
relations should deteriorate and lead to an unpredictable 
misfortune. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7346 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas083_c_94017" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-083 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  29 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Offices in Osaka Raided by Police </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Offices in Osaka Raided by Police </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Foreign Ministry Protests </H4>

<F P=102> SK2904050194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0452 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2904050194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["DPRK Foreign Ministry Spokesman Urges Japanese Authorities </F>
To Stop Crackdown on Chongnyon and Apologize for It" -- KCNA 
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 29 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the 
DPRK Foreign Ministry in a statement today demanded that the 
Japanese authorities ponder over the grave consequences to be 
entailed by their reckless acts, immediately stop their 
crackdown on the General Association of Korean residents in 
Japan (Chongnyon) and Koreans in Japan and apologize for it. 
  Some time ago, the Japanese authorities sent scores of 
mobile 
police vehicles and some 1,000 policemen who encircled the Osaka 
Prefectural headquarters of Chongnyon and forcibly searched 
office rooms of the headquarters, residences of its leading 
officials and branch offices. Earlier, rightwing gangsters 
under the manipulation of the authorities swarmed to a central 
organ of Chongnyon and its affiliated organizations and kicked 
up a row, even murdering a businessman of Chongnyon. 
  "This is a hostile act of encroaching upon the sovereignty 
of 
Chongnyon and crudely violating the democratic national rights 
of Koreans in Japan and a challenge to the DPRK which cannot be 
overlooked," the statement says, and goes on: 
  "We cannot but take a serious note of the fact that the 
Japanese authorities are intensifying their suppression of 
Chongnyon and Koreans in Japan, while intentionally aggravating 
the situation over the fictitious 'nuclear issue' of the DPRK at 
the instigation of the United States. 
  "Chongnyon is a peaceloving organization whose activities 
are 
officially recognized by the Japanese authorities and the 
Japanese law and which enjoys full support of many countries and 
organizations in the world. 
  "There is neither reason nor ground for Chongnyon to be an 
object of crackdown by the Japanese authorities. 
  "Moreover, Koreans in Japan are innocent people who were 
forcibly taken to Japan and subjected to hard toil under the 
brutal Japanese imperialist rule, and their descendants. 
Therefore, special protection must be granted to them by the 
Japanese authorities. 
  "Far from apologizing for and liquidating the past crimes 
committed against the Korean people, however, the Japanese 
authorities are engaging in suppression of Koreans in Japan and 
their legitimate organizations. This is an unpardonable act. 
  "We will consider any crackdown on Chongnyon an encroachment 
upon the dignity and sovereignty of our Republic and decisively 
counter it." 
  The statement expresses the hope that all the progressive 
personages and broad sections of people in Japan and the world 
will continue to express support and solidarity for the 
righteous activities of Chongnyon for its democratic national 
rights and national reunification. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7347 </DOCNO>
