<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cuban Press Agency Director Discusses Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cuban Press Agency Director Discusses Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2604104994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1017 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2604104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 26 (KCNA) -- "President Kim Il-song 
who has been active as an outstanding statesman for many years, 
performing great exploits in the struggle for the freedom and 
independence of the country, is a great leader of the present 
time who is famous worldwide," said Pedro Margolles Villanueva, 
director general of the PRENSA LATINA of Cuba, who visited Korea. 
  Giving his impressions of Korea here, he said, "When I had 
an 
audience of President Kim Il-song, I could deeply feel once 
again comrade president's unshakable revolutionary will to 
defend the cause of socialism with no retreat before the 
imperialists and his strong and resolute position never to 
pardon any invading enemy." 
  "Under the wise guidance of the great Comrade Kim Il-song 
and 
dear Comrade Kim Chong-il, enormous achievements have been made 
in socialist construction of Korea and the Korean people have 
wrought miracles which no one else can effect over the 40 odd 
years since the ceasefire," he said. 
  The director general of the PRENSA LATINA added that 
wonderful and magnificent grand monuments have taken shape in 
different parts of the country, Pyongyang has turned into the 
most beautiful city and all people lead a happy life with stable 
jobs. 
  "Now the West is alleging that the DPRK is stepping up `war 
preparations.' But it is quite contrary to the fact," he said, 
adding that Korea is promoting peaceful construction, not war 
preparations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

