<H3> <TI>   Papers Mark Sierra Leone Independence Day </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Papers Mark Sierra Leone Independence Day </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2704103594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1021 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2704103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 27 (KCNA) -- Papers here today 
dedicate articles to the 33rd anniversary of the independence of 
Sierra Leone. 
  A by-lined article of MINJU CHOSON says that the Sierra 
Leonean people have worked to build a new independent and 
prospering society after independence. 
  It notes: 
  Sierra Leone is developing relations with many countries, 
pursuing a non-aligned policy externally. 
  The Democratic People's Republic of Korea established 
diplomatic ties with Sierra Leone in October 1971. Since then 
travels and contacts have been frequent and friendly relations 
further developed between the two peoples. 
  Believing that the friendly and cooperative relations 
between 
the two countries will grow stronger and develop in accordance 
with the idea of independence, peace and friendship, the Korean 
people wish the Sierra Leonean people new achievements in the 
efforts for the independent development of the country, the 
article says. NODONG SINMUN carries an article introducing the 
change of Sierra Leone. 

</TEXT>

