<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Kim Il-song Hails Afghan President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Kim Il-song Hails Afghan President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2704110694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1044 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2704110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 27 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il-song 
of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea today sent a 
message of greetings to Borhanoddin Rabbani, president of the 
Islamic State of Afghanistan, on the day of the victory of the 
Islamic revolution in Afghanistan. 
  President Kim Il-song in the message wished the president 
and 
people of Afghanistan success in their work for national 
reconciliation and stability of the country and expressed the 
belief that the friendly relations between the two countries 
would continue to develop. 

</TEXT>

