<F P=102>   BK2804095194 Hanoi VNA in English 0556 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2804095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 28 -- Kim Il-song, secretary general 
of the Workers's Party and president of the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea (DPRK) has received the visiting delegation of 
the Communist Party of Vietnam led by Hong Ha, secretary of the 
CPVCC [Communist Party of Vietnam Central Committee]. 
  President Kim Il-song warmly welcomed the Vietnamese party 
delegation's visit as a manifestation of the strengthening of 
the relations between the two parties, and peoples. He asked 
Secretary Hong Ha to convey his best regards to party General 
Secretary Do Muoi, President Le Duc Anh and other Vietnamese 
party leaders. 
  He also expressed his pleasure at the fine development of 
the 
relationship between the two parties and peoples, and his wish 
for new step of development in the DPRK-Vietnam relations. 
  For his part, Mr. Hong Ha conveyed best regards of party 
General Secretary Do Muoi and President Le Duc Anh to President 
Kim Il-song, Kim Chong-il and other Korean party leaders. He 
affirmed that Vietnamese party's policy is to enhance the 
traditional friendly relations of the two peoples, and for peace 
cooperation and development in the region and in the world as a 
whole. 

</TEXT>

