<H3> <TI>   Syrian Ambassador Meets With Yi In-mo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Syrian Ambassador Meets With Yi In-mo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2904043794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0421 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2904043794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 29 (KCNA) -- Syrian Ambassador to 
Korea Yasir Farah and his wife on April 28 met with Yi In-mo, a 
former war correspondent of the Korean People's Army, who is 
known as an incarnation of faith and will. 
  The ambassador said the Syrian people were struck with 
admiration at Yi In-mo who did not abandon his creed as a 
communist while being kept behind bars for a long time, not 
yielding to the barbarous suppression by the enemy. 
  Recalling that the great leader President Kim Il-song called 
on Yi In-mo in his sickbed last year, so busy as he was, and 
showed deep solicitude for him, the ambassador said he was 
deeply moved by the president's loving care for his 
revolutionary soldiers. 
  Yi In-mo said that the great leader President Kim Il-song 
and 
the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il are pursuing benevolent 
politics and independent politics and that they are the life and 
soul of the Korean people. 
  The guests presented souvenirs to Yi In-mo. 

</TEXT>

