<F P=102> SK2704103394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1012 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2704103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 27 (KCNA) -- Bulletins were brought 
out by the Algeria-Korea Friendship Club on April 12 and by the 
Burundi-Korea Friendship Association on April 13 in celebration 
of April 15. 
  Carried in the bulletin of the Algeria-Korea Friendship Club 
are articles titled "President Kim Il-song Who Has Been Devoting 
His Whole Life for the People," "`10-point Programme of the 
Great Unity of the Whole Nation for the Reunification of the 
Country' Put Forward by President Kim Il-song" and "Signature 
Campaign Supporting Peace and Reunification of Korea". 
  The bulletin published by the Burundi-Korea Friendship 
Association came off the press under the title "Best Wishes for 
Longevity to President Kim Il-song". 
  The Venezuelan Committee for the Reunification of Korea 
published the April issue of its bulletin. 
  Conveyed in the bulletin is news that political figures and 
organisations of India and Zimbabwe called for grandly 
celebrating April 15. 

</TEXT>

