<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Kim Il-song Birthday </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Kim Il-song Birthday </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Observances Abroad Reported </H4>

<F P=102> SK2804105394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1013 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2804105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 28 (KCNA) -- Functions took place 
in various countries to celebrate the birthday of the great 
leader President Kim Il-song. 
  An April 15 celebration weekly function was held in Lima, 
Peru, under the co-sponsorship of political parties and 
organizations. 
  Speaking at the function, Angel Castro Lavarello, president 
of the National Executive Committee of the Left Revolutionary 
Union of Peru, said: 
  "The great leader President Kim Il-song is a genius of 
revolution and construction who has built Korea into a powerful 
socialist country, independent, self-supporting and self-reliant 
in national defence, and an iron-willed brilliant commander who 
defeated two imperialisms in one generation and is firmly 
defending the cause of socialism. 
  "He is the lodestar of Korean reunification who put forth 
the 
three principles of independence, peaceful reunification and 
great national unity, the proposal for founding the Democratic 
Confederal Republic of Koryo and the 10-point programme of the 
great unity of the whole nation and is leading the whole nation 
to carry them into effect." 
  A letter to President Kim Il-song was adopted at the opening 
ceremony of the function amidst an enthusiastic applause. 
  A meeting was held at the Jilin Yuwen Middle School in 
China, 
a Korean photo and handicraft exhibition and a film show in 
Giurgiu County, Romania, a lecture and a photo exhibition at the 
peace hall in Hungary, and a Korean book presentation ceremony 
in Paris, France. 
  Cultural functions took place in Baktapur, Nepal and at the 
folklore museum theatre in Peru in celebration of the April 15 
fete. 

</TEXT>

