<H4>    Cilreco Issues Bulletin </H4>

<F P=102> SK2904103694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1010 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2904103694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 29 (KCNA) -- The International 
Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea (Cilreco) 
brought out a special issue of its bulletin on the occasion of 
the birthday of the great leader President Kim Il-song. 
  Under the title "Highest Homage to President Kim Il-song on 
His 82nd Birthday" the bulletin gives sub-titles "We Wish 
President Kim Il-song good health and a long life", "Role and 
Feats of President Kim Il-song for the Accomplishment of the 
Cause of Korea's Independent and Peaceful Reunification" and 
"President Kim Il-song's Just and Feasible Proposal for Founding 
the Democratic Confederal Republic of Koryo". 
  It pays highest homage to President Kim Il-song who is 
making 
contributions to the cause for human progress and building a 
peaceful world. 
  His proposals for Korean reunification opened up realistic 
prospects for ending the tragedy of division, notes the bulletin. 
  It stresses that more widespread international solidarity 
movements would be conducted in support of the Korean people's 
just struggle to carry into effect the 10-point programme, a 
grand programme of peaceful reunification through the great 
unity of the whole Korean nation. 
  On the same occasion, bulletins were issued by the 
Guyana-Korea Friendship Association and the Zimbabwe-Korea 
solidarity and Friendship Association. 

</TEXT>

