<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Reportedly Quoted in U.S. Papers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Reportedly Quoted in U.S. Papers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2604050794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0452 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2604050794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 26 (KCNA) -- The famous work of the 
great leader President Kim Il-song "Answers to the Questions 
Raised by the Japanese NHK News Coverage Group" was reported by 
U.S. papers. 
  INTERNATIONAL HERALD TRIBUNE April 19, carrying the answers, 
said President Kim Il-song has been leading Korea for nearly 
half a century. 
  The paper quoted President Kim Il-song as saying that the 
United States is putting pressure on the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea which has no nuclear weapons on absurd charges 
while trying to dismiss with the word "withdrawal" the question 
of the nuclear weapons it has actually shipped into South Korea 
and that the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula can be solved 
only through direct talks between the DPRK and the U.S. 
  On the same day WASHINGTON POST, reporting a detailed gist 
of 
the work of the great leader, stressed that President Kim 
Il-song is the most veteran head of state in the world. 

</TEXT>

