<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Death Sentence Given for Destroying State Property </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Death Sentence Given for Destroying State Property </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2904071994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2904071994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 26 April in Tu Hoa Township, the Quang Ninh 
People's Court tried eight defendants on charges of destroying 
important national security projects and handling property 
obtained from other people's criminal activities. 
  The court sentenced Vu Van Vuong to death for his leading 
role in the conspiracy to destroy high-voltage power line 
supports. It sentenced Khong Tiet Bao to life imprisonment for 
destroying important projects and national security equipment. 
Six other defendants, guilty of handling property obtained from 
other people's criminal activities, received prison terms 
ranging from two to six years. 

</TEXT>

