<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ammunition Siezed in Ho Chi Minh City Customs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ammunition Siezed in Ho Chi Minh City Customs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2904022594 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2904022594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the 28 April edition of LAO DONG 
newspaper, Customs officers in Ho Chi Minh City recently 
discovered a container sent via the United Kingdom by an 
overseas Vietnamese living in America to a Vietnamese citizen 
with registered residence in Ho Chi Minh City. 
  Various items in the container include air guns, hunting 
guns, ammunition for hunting guns, 4.5 caliber ammunition, 
grenades, two pairs of binoculars, two sets of walkie-talkies, 
one helicopter rotor, one diver's suit, two diver's air tanks, 
one mine-clearing machine, several other items, and 19 packs of 
books and papers, the contents of which are being examined by 
authorized agencies. 
  All the exhibits and related documents have been transferred 
to Ho Chi Minh City police for further investigation. 

</TEXT>

