<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Northern Provinces Form Special Economic Region </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Northern Provinces Form Special Economic Region </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2904111494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 28 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2904111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An integrated economic region for the 
industrialization and market orientation will be formed by 
Hanoi, Haiphong, and some other provinces in north of Hanoi. 
The project is called planning orientation for key northern 
areas. The region has great resources of minerals and labor as 
well as enormous potential and tourism development as it 
accounts for 60 percent of the whole country's hydropower 
potential. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7395 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas083_n_94015" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-083 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  28 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Premier on Actions Against Illicit Car Imports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Premier on Actions Against Illicit Car Imports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2904103794 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2904103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The newspaper LAO DONG on 28 April reported that 
Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet held a working session with the 
chairman of the Song Be Provincial People's Committee regarding 
the illicit import of 273 cars. 
  After hearing leading comrades of the Song Be Provincial 
People's Committee criticize themselves for the wrongdoings they 
committed in legitimizing and allowing the operation of 273 
illicitly imported cars -- the responsibility for which rests 
chiefly with the chairman of the provincial people's committee 
and his deputies who were directly in charge of this case -- the 
prime minister asked the chairman of the Song Be Provincial 
People's Committee to scrupulously carry out self-criticism, 
report the results to the provincial party standing committee, 
and propose the form and extent of disciplinary actions to be 
taken against the provincial people's committee collectively. 
  As for the chairman and the two vice chairmen of the 
provincial people's committee directly involved in this case, 
they must scrupulously review their wrongdoings, propose the 
extent of disciplinary actions to be taken against themselves, 
for instance, resigning from their present positions so other 
comrades can replace them. This must be carried out in such a 
way as to ensure scrupulous law enforcement. 
  Those state organs such as tax, security police, customs, 
and 
trade organs in Song Be that failed to take preventive measures 
against this wrongdoing and to report it to higher management 
organs and that are found to be involved in the wrongdoings must 
also ascertain their specific responsibilities so appropriate 
disciplinary actions can be taken against them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7396 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas083_n_94016" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-083 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  26 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Overseas Vietnamese Receive Tax Incentive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Overseas Vietnamese Receive Tax Incentive </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2704163194 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2704163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The State Commission for Cooperation and Investment 
and the Overseas Vietnamese Central Department has just issued a 
circular to encourage more overseas Vietnamese investment. 
  According to the circular, all economic units with more than 
half of their capital coming from overseas Vietnamese will enjoy 
a 20 percent reduction in income tax, except for those units 
already taxed at the concessional rate of only 10 percent. When 
their concessional tax has expired, they will pay income tax at 
the 20 percent rate. 
  When transferring profits abroad, the economic units of 
overseas Vietnamese will enjoy the lowest tax rate for profit 
transfers, 5 percent, as stipulated by the Investment Law. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

