<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fleet Commander Inaugrates Two Naval Units </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fleet Commander Inaugrates Two Naval Units </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2904010094 Jakarta ANTARA in English 1059 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2904010094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta ANTARA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jakarta, Apr 28 (OANA/ANTARA) -- Indonesia's 
Western Regional Fleet Commander-in-Chief Rear Admiral Aried 
Kushariadi inaugurated the new amphibious squad and exercise 
fleet command here Thursday. 
  The two new units will strengthen the naval operation in the 
western region of the archipelago and will consolidate the 
so-called "integrated fleet system" of the Indonesian Navy. 
  The Western Fleet commander-in-chief also swore in the 
commanders of the new units -- Colonel Sumarjo appointed as the 
amphibious ships squad commander and Colonel Fakhmi Jamaris as 
exercise fleet commander. 
  The Western Regional Fleet was established in 1985, while 
the 
Eastern Regional Fleet has been in existence since the country's 
independence. 
  According to Kushariadi, two more squads will be set up -- 
the escort ships squad and the minesweepers squad -- following 
the arrival of 39 warships purchased by the Indonesian Navy from 
Germany. 
  Of the 39 warships, nine minesweepers, five corvettes, and 
three amphibious LSTs (landing ship tanks), have already arrived 
here. 

</TEXT>

