<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaders Meet With Albright, Shalikashvili </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leaders Meet With Albright, Shalikashvili </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3003192394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3003192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The official delegation of the United States led by 
Madeleine Albright, U.S. ambassador to the United Nations, and 
General John Shalikashvili, commander of the Joint Chiefs of 
Staff of the U.S. Armed Forces, arrived in Sarajevo this 
afternoon. The delegation was received by President Alija 
Izetbegovic of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency, Presidency 
member Ejup Ganic, Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris 
Silajdzic, Bosnia-Herzegovina Foreign Minister Irfan 
Ljubijankic, and Defense Minister Hamdija Hadzihasanovic. 
  General John Shalikashvili held talks with Army General 
Rasim 
Delic, commander of the General Staff of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Army. It is the greatest honor for the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 
to be visited by General Shalikashvili, General Rasim Delic told 
B-H PRESS after the meeting. The talks concerned the course of 
the negotiations and the process leading to peace in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. General Delic stated: 
  We should say that we have the full support of the United 
States, both the U.S. political and military leadership, to 
reach an agreement as soon as possible that would guarantee a 
just peace. We said that we were interested only in just peace 
in Bosnia-Herzegovina. In that respect we expect that the 
support of the United States will be the deciding factor in 
bringing about the kind of peace that our people want, General 
Delic said. 

</TEXT>

