<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Attack on Gorazde Continues; Casualties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Attack on Gorazde Continues; Casualties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103091994 </F>
<F P=103> AU3103091994 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Network in Serbo-Croatian at 0800 GMT on 31 March reports 
fighting in the following parts of the country: 
  The correspondent from Gorazde, Enes Musovic, reports that 
"the chetniks have been pounding all lines of defense of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army fighters with artillery of the largest 
calibers the entire night." As he continues to say, "the 
situation is extremely fierce on all lines of Gorazde's defense 
on the right bank of the Drina River" while "on the left bank of 
the Drina River the chetniks are attacking from Ustipraca and 
Mesici at Kopaci and Trovrh." "From 1900 last night to 0800 this 
morning one person died and eight sustained serious injuries. 
Yesterday and the day before, 15 people were killed and 40 
injured." 
  "The activities of the Serbian aggressor against the Bihac 
district have continued overnight and this morning," 
correspondent Mirza Sadikovic says. "Yesterday, in the early 
evening, Karadzic's terrorists attacked the center of Bihac 
[words indistinct] as well as the hospital. New material damage 
was caused and, according to incomplete reports, there are 
injured civilians. In the course of the night, the intensity of 
shelling subsided a little because of low flights by NATO 
aircraft." "In other areas," Sadikovic goes on, "antiaircraft 
arms' fire and sniper fire were observed in the course of the 
night and since early morning." "On the separating lines with 
the paramilitary formations of the so-called Kladusa 
autonomists, there have been provocative attacks with mortars 
and hill guns at various intervals, launched from the area of 
Krivaja and [word indistinct] in the Kladusa commune." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

