<H3> <TI>   Crvenkovski Welcomes U.S. Mediation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crvenkovski Welcomes U.S. Mediation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2903194494 Skopje MIC in English 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2903194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Stevo Crvenkovski: `Little Can Be </F>
Done Under Pressure'"] 
  [Text] After the talks with Matthew Nimetz, Macedonia's 
[The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] Foreign 
Minister Stevo Crvenkovski stated that Macedonia was satisfied 
that the United States has its own mediator in the 
Macedonian-Greek dispute, who was in tight coordination with the 
UN mediator Cyrus Vance. 
  "This way, President Clinton will have the opportunity to 
become closer acquainted with the dispute between Macedonia and 
Greece. We believe that the best place for the continuation of 
the negotiations is the United Nations. This way we have a 
process which can eventually result in the continuation of the 
negotiations. Under the pressure of embargo, little can be 
done." 

</TEXT>

