<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peterle Requests Lifting of Arms Embargo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peterle Requests Lifting of Arms Embargo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3003151294 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1330 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3003151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Slovene </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Lojze Peterle has sent a letter to 
UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali and foreign ministers 
of the UN Security Concil member-states, asking that the UN 
Security Council lift the arms embargo. 
  The minister pointed out that the situation in Slovenia is 
perfectly peaceful, that Slovenia is a sovereign and independent 
country and a UN member, which consistently meets all 
international obligations. Our country demonstrates a high 
level of political stability and observation of human rights. 
It is a member of the Council of Europe, has signed the 
Partnership for Peace plan, and is just about to commence 
negotiations on associate membership in the European Union, 
Minister Peterle among other things emphasized in his letter. 

</TEXT>

