<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berisha Warns About `All-Out War' in Balkans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berisha Warns About `All-Out War' in Balkans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103134794 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3103134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["I.M."-initialled report: "Berisha Warns Against Balkans </F>
War"] 
  [Text] Vienna -- "The outbreak of hostilities in Kosovo 
would have a destabilizing effect on the neighboring states of 
the former Yugoslavia and particularly Albania, and an all-out 
war in the Balkans would be unavoidable." On his way home from 
London, Albania's President Sali Berisha stopped in Vienna to 
give a news conference. In London he did not only discuss 
bilateral relations with the main focus on the economy, but he 
also submitted the proposal that a relaxation of the UN 
sanctions against Serbia should be linked with a solution to the 
Kosovo problem, the president stressed. Berisha stated that 
Prime Minister Major and Foreign Secretary Hurd had shown 
understanding. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

