<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Employees Declare `Strike Alert' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Employees Declare `Strike Alert' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3003213094 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1600 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3003213094 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Independent Trade Union of Radio Employees has 
declared a strike alert. The nearly 100 trade union members 
also decided at a meeting in the afternoon that next Thursday 
they will protest against the dismissals which have been 
announced with a demonstration at the radio. The Independent 
Trade Union of Radio Employees also protested against the fact 
that the radio leadership, obviously for political reasons, has 
launched disciplinary procedure against Laszlo Gyori, chairman 
of the trade union and of the strike committee, and Peter 
Borenics, chairman of the Council of Public Employees. The 
Independent Trade Union of Radio Employees has confirmed its 
previous stance that the illegal measures of the radio bosses 
harm the listeners most of all, because such moves endanger 
objective information and the implementation of the radio's 
public service tasks. 

</TEXT>

