<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   HVO Closes Zepce Concentration Camp </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    HVO Closes Zepce Concentration Camp </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0104105394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0104105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The signing of the agreement and the promulgation of 
the Constitution of the Federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina are 
already yielding good results in the Zepce Commune. After the 
cooperation in the field between the Army of Bosnia-Herzegovina 
and the Croatian Defense Council [HVO] was established and 
(?two-day) mutual visits of civilian population made possible, 
the HVO concentration camp in Zepce was closed yesterday. Under 
the auspices of the UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] Sector 
Command in the region, the HVO Command released all the 
remaining prisoners, members of the Army of Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
who then freely decided to travel to free territories or to 
remain in Zepce with their families. 

</TEXT>

