<H3> <TI>   Receives Shalikashvili, Albright </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Receives Shalikashvili, Albright </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3003104594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1000 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3003104594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Franjo Tudjman, president of the Republic of 
Croatia, today received in the Presidential Palace [in Zagreb] 
General John Shalikashvili, chairman of the joint chiefs of 
staff of the United States, and Madeleine Albright, U.S. 
permanent representative at the UN. 
  The talks were also attended on the U.S. side by the U.S. 
Ambassador in Croatia Peter Galbraith, and Charles Redman, the 
special envoy of the U.S. President. The Croatian delegation 
comprises Dr. Mate Granic, Dr. Jure Radic, Gojko Susak [defense 
minister], Hrvoje Sarinic [the Croatian president's national 
security adviser], Janko Bobetko, and Zvonimir (Crnjenko). 
  Before his meeting with President Tudjman, Gen. 
Shalikashvili 
had a meeting at the UN base in Pleso [near Zagreb airport] with 
UNPROFOR [UN Protection Force] Commander in Chief Gen. Bertrand 
de Lapresle, and he also visited the U.S. military hospital. 

</TEXT>

