<H3> <TI>   Granic Receives Diplomats Following Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Granic Receives Diplomats Following Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3103174894 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3103174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mate Granic, deputy prime minister and foreign 
minister of the Republic of Croatia, has presented to members of 
the Diplomatic Corps accredited to Croatia copies of the text of 
the cease-fire agreement signed yesterday between 
representatives of the Croatian authorities and Serb rebels from 
the temporarily occupied areas of the Republic of Croatia. 
  Minister Granic said Croatia was ready to take on a 
constructive role in negotiations with the Serb rebels and that 
it expected further progress in the implementation of the 
agreement and in the overall process of the peaceful 
reintegration of the occupied areas in the constitutional and 
legal system of the Republic of Croatia. 
  Granic also briefed the diplomats on the results so far of 
the implementation of the Washington agreement. All clashes 
between Muslim Bosnians and Croats in Bosnia-Herzegovina have 
ceased and humanitarian deliveries have improved. At the same 
time deputies of the constituent assembly accepted the 
Constitution of Bosnia-Herzegovina in Sarajevo yesterday. 
  Granic added that he expected representatives of the Serbian 
people to soon join in the negotiations on the peaceful 
settlement of the crisis in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

